<Author>sredheada
<Content>If Hell had a hotel....this would be it! We were given room # 243. Room was very dirty. Carpet filthy and stained. Marks all over walls. Phone was so dirty I didnt want to touch it. I used toilet paper to hold the receiver since there was no tissue provided in my room. We killed 4 cockroaches in the bathroom upon arrival into the room and flushed them down the toilet. We realized we didn鈥檛 have enough towels. We called down to the front desk to ask for additional towels but were told the hotel did not have additional towels. So we made the best of the situation and shared. We never did get additional towels; even the next day we had to use the same towels.  After dark, the cockroaches really started to come out. Crawling on the walls, on the desk area, on the bathroom vanity, on our bedside table, just about everywhere. We were horrified! I called down to the front desk and asked to change rooms. I was told I could not as nothing was available. I started calling other hotels in the area, at my expense; however, because of cruises going out everything was sold out. I called down to the front desk again. I asked for some raid or even a fly swatter. Days Inn had neither. The desk clerk said nothing could be done until tomorrow when I could talk to the manager. I was stuck! We killed 19 cockroaches before retiring that evening. We could have killed more, however, many were too fast for us. I awoke at 3am. I killed several more cockroaches. Several crawling on the phone, radio, my water glass, and the bedside table. I killed as many as I could but they would just run behind the bedside table. I killed one crawling on my headboard. I shuttered to think my head was just there! At that time my mother woke up because she felt something crawling on her. Sure enough...............there was a cockroach in her bed!!! Needless to say we didn鈥檛 get much sleep that night. At 8am I immediately went down to the front desk to speak to the manager. I was told no manager would not be on duty until 4pm. I again asked if I could change rooms. I was again told nothing was available but after 3pm something might become available.  I went to talk to the manager at the front desk at 4pm. I was told, sorry I was given wrong information and that the manger would not be in till 4pm the next day, Sunday. I again told the desk clerk I needed to change rooms because of the cockroaches. Again this was denied. I implored him. I told him the room was infested with cockroaches. He didn鈥檛 say a word. He just shook his head and shrugged his shoulders. Apparently my request that morning to change rooms when someone else checked out was denied. Again I was stuck! I went back to my room and killed all the roaches I could find. I also found several dead ones on the floor between the bedside table and the bed. So much for vacuuming. It was another rather sleepless night. The next morning I was never so glad to check out of a hotel!  At checkout the lobby was full of people complaining and waiting in line. They complained about not having enough towels, dirty rooms, incorrect and extra room charges, etc.  How much would you pay to stay in a filthy hotel room infested with cockroaches? $89.00? $59.00? $44.00? By the way, I got the last two rates from poeple who were in line with me at the front desk. They stayed the same night as I did in rooms with, reportedly, much fewer roaches. On the nights I stayed in this room I would look down into the parking lot from the window. I would wish I could sleep in one of those cars parked there instead of that room. At least they would have been roach free. We slept with all the lights on in the room hoping this would lessen the cockroaches from coming out. Judging from the amount of cockroaches, I don鈥檛 think this did any good. I always wore flip flops on the carpet in the room because I knew it was filthy. My mother walked on it with her bare feet. After a few minutes I noticed the bottom of her feet were black with dirt. She went and washed them in the bathtub. The water turned black and so did the soap. The toilet seat was broken. It kept slipping off the base. My disabled mother actually fell off the toilet because of this. It is a good thing she was not hurt. I also fell off the seat but I was able to catch myself in time. We requested a wake up call at 7:00am with the front desk. A few minutes later they called us back reconfirming our wake up call. He said he was talking to someone and forgot the time we requested. We told him again 7:00am. We received no wake up call. It is a good thing we woke up ourselves that morning. If I am expected to pay $89.00 plus tax for this hotel room, Days Inn should put on their web site, -plenty of roaches -no towels-unreliable shuttle, may be cancelled at the last minute -Clerks will tell you that management is available but management will never be available-Wear shoes because carpets are filthy-You can request a wake up call but you wont get it Everyone waiting in the lobby agreed when I suggested that Days Inn get their name off of this hotel. After returning home I contacted the hotel directly and Days Inn. Days Inn was no help at all and told me to contact the hotel directly. The hotel's response was to offer me 10% off on my next stay there. They couldnt pay me enough to ever stay at this hotel from hell again. 
