<Content>It's a welfare hotel people We were supposed to stay at this hotel for one night before leaving for a cruise. Thank God it was only night. I've heard the saying, you get what you pay for, but if this hotel is any indication of that saying, it should have been free.We were told the two rooms we reserved would be right next door to each other. They were opposite ends of the hall.One member of our group waited an hour for the shuttle (old lady in a van) to pick her up from the airport. The shuttle never arrived and she ended up taking a cab.Another member from our group waited 50 minutes for the van and when it finally arrived the driver spent the entire ride cursing someone out on her cellphone and when they got to the hotel the driver dropped his luggage out on the ground. And the van has the nerve to have tips are greatly appreciated posted all over the !@#$% van.When one member of our group entered the room he was greeted by roaches crawling across a piece of furniture which I can only guess was a dresser with only 2 drawers in it.The towels in the bathroom were wet.The bathroom floor was stickyI walked around the room, on carpet, in my socks and had to throw them away by the next morning because they looked like I had been walking around outside.The bed had two flat sheets on it instead of a fitted and flat sheet.The comforter had a wierd order that came from God only knows what.They were having a children's party complete with hotdogs and hamburgers in a room down the hall and some little kid about 3 or so wasn't being watched and wandered into our room.We didn't even bother to take our clothes off to go to bed, who knows what was on the sheets.The bathtub took 45 minutes to drain the water from a shower.The back of the hotel faces the highway so you hear cars all night long.There is no order to the shuttle service. It's survival of the fittest when it comes to who gets on first.This isn't worth the inexpensive room. Spend the extra money and stay somewhere else. 
