<Content>Scarey! Days Inn Civic Center- Miami, FloridaI was looking for somewhere cheap to stay for one night before I left for a cruise. I thought the Days Inn name could be trusted and the hotel website looked pretty decent. When calling for information the front desk staff was quite curt and I was disconnected on another different occasion (which is frustrating when calling long distance). When picked up at the airport by our free shuttle, I found myself getting into the only Days Inn van that had a dent in it (Days Inn vans for other Days Inn locations were also circling the airport collecting guests) which should have tipped me off. We got to the hotel and once again the night front desk staff were not helpful, often spoke to each other in another language in front of me, and rolled their eyes at requests I made or questions I asked. The elevator, ice machine, and in-room safe were all broken. We also found a few bugs scurry past at various times in the evening. Knowing that there were 3 of us staying in the room, we still had to ask, more than once, for extra towels. The location was inconvenient as there were no restaurants within walking distance. Not reccommended! Pay the extra few dollars and go to a different location. 
