<Content>Never Stay Here! Worst pit we have ever experienced -- I can not imagine how this dump deserves any stars at all, let alone 2 stars! I didn't expect luxury, but did expect a normal clean/no-frills Days Inn. Our room had no functioning air conditioning, so we were finally moved (at midnight!) after jumping through hoops and putting up a fuss. The good room was dingy and dirty; lamps didn't work, alarm clock didn't work, threadbare linens. The staff was rude and spoke no English at all. Scary part of town with no restaurants in the vicinity, so nowhere to get a bite to eat at night. Very tacky attached restaurant (only breakfast and dinner) was way overpriced and had only one overworked, churlish waiter. This was a quick one night stay between arrival in Miami and leaving next morning on a cruise, so -- thank goodness -- didn't have to be here long! Next time we will pay a little bit more! Days Inn should revoke their brand from this dump.I sure wish I had discovered Trip Advisor before I booked this room! 
