<Content>A piece of SHIZZNICK!@ Anyone looking for a decent hotel this is NOT it. I stayed her in October precruise. It started off bad when I checked in. I bought my 2 nights stay through American Airlines, which was prepaid for. When I checked in they had my reservation but had told me that it wasn't paid for. I explained to them it was already prepaid and I had my confirmation slip from American Airlines as proof. This was still not satisfactory to them. The front desk had to call AA and AA confirmed this. Days Inn is still telling me it isnt paid for. This goes on for about 20 min. Everyone in my group has already gotten their keys to their room and left. I asked the front desk clerk what is taken so long to figure this out and she tells me that someone is going to call again but I can call myself on my cell phone if I'm in a rush. Yeah I'm in a rush. I just got off a long plane ride. I would like to freshen up. That's not asking much!!!!! Some customer service huh. Finally the manager comes out to deal with the situation. And it's taken care of. When I get to my room the room was dirty. The carpet was very stained and dirty. The bathroom was not that clean. It had mildew. Etc., Etc., My friend said that in her room the sheets were dirty when she checked in. When she noticed them at night when she went to bed she called them three times and no one came to change them. The second time when she called the front desk they told her we are really busy down here. i'll call you back click. The girl hung up on her. After the third time my friend was so angry and tired she took the sheets down to the front desk in her nightgown and slippers and demanded new ones. Now this was her pre wedding night. Who's needs the STRESS!!To sum it up. I will never go to a Days Inn again. And I don't recommend this Days Inn to anyone else. 
