<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Rip off/ misadvertisement/ Civic Center This place is a rip off and not what they advertise. The 'FREE' shuttle service has some catches, they don't mention this on their website. One van is for the airport and the other is for the port. If you expect a free shuttle to Bayside Marketplace, think again, it only runs at 9:30 and 5:30 although we never seen a shuttle go there.My husband and I were witness to a lady complaining about the shuttle service, she waited two hours at the airport and ended up taking a taxi (so did we and many others in our party, so we could relate to being mad about it). Well, she asked for some kind of compensation and was told he could do nothing, she went on complaining and another lady behind the desk talked about her in spanish and told him to give her 5 bucks so she would shut her mouth. This should never be done by anyone!!! They didn't realize that someone else may understand or they simply didn't care.We stayed the first two nights before our cruise in a first floor room by the pool and it was much better and less noisy than the night we spent on the third floor facing the busy road. In both rooms, the carpets were filthy, but the towels and bedding were clean. There were no roaches or other bugs in either room. The room facing the street was VERY noisy, so if you can get a room by the pool, it's much nicer. The view looks nicer too.The restaurant is overpriced, but not so bad food. My husband and I took the metro and buses to go places. No one seems to smile, but then again we were the ones on vacation and with more reason to smile. It wasn't the worst place, but definately not worth the money. I think the staff could use a few classes in courtesy and respect. By smiling and being courteous, I bet they could have made a few people happier. I would not want to go back there. I felt like I was putting them out by using thier hotel!This hotel category should have Civic Center listed also, cause I missed the reviews before our trip. I think we still would have stayed here, but would never consider staying there again...it's not worth the stress and/or hassle. Everyone is charged a safe fee, but the safe doesn't work in the rooms. Make sure you have them remove the charge!!!!Taxi to Bayside -- 12.50 (or you can bargain with the drivers for less)Taxi to Airport -- I heard was 21.00Taxi to Port --- ?? 
